, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Diagnostic characters of Taiwanoshaira taipingshanensis sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C penis, apex, dorsal view D penis, base, dorsal view E penis, lateral view F endophallic sclerites, dorsal view G ditto, lateral view H gonocoxae, from Yuanyanghu (鴛鴦湖) I same, from Taipingshan (太平山) J abdominal ventrite VIII, from Yuanyanghu (鴛鴦湖) K same, from Taipingshan (太平山) L spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.944.53099.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/426850" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">7J-K</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Diagnostic characters of Taiwanoshaira tsoui sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C penis, dorsal view D penis, lateral view E endophallic sclerites, from Meifeng (梅峰), dorsal view F ditto, lateral view G same, from Peitungyanshan (北東眼山), dorsal H ditto, lateral view I samel, from Tahsuehshan (大雪山), J ditto, laeral view K same, form Taipingshan (太平山), dorsal L ditto, lateral view M gonocoxae, from Hsiaofengkou (小風口) N same, from Taipingshan (太平山) O abdominal ventrite VIII, from Peitungyanshan (北東眼山) P same, from Taipingshan (太平山) Q spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.944.53099.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/426851" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">8O-P</figureCitation>
) well sclerotized, with several short setae at apex, spiculum elongate. Spermathecal receptaculum (Figs 
