<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="129" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="129">
Adults of 
<taxonomicName authority="Lee &amp; Beenen, 2020" authorityName="Lee &amp; Beenen" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Taiwanoshaira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Taiwanoshaira" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Taiwanoshaira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. lack metathoracic wings, but elytra present, which completely cover the abdomen. Furthermore, the morphology of the elytra differs from that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Maulik, 1936" authorityName="Maulik" authorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Shaira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Shaira" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Shaira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In 
<taxonomicName authority="Maulik, 1936" authorityName="Maulik" authorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Shaira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Shaira" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Shaira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the elytra possess an elongate ridge from the humeral area to the apex, dividing the elytra into a horizontal part and a lateral inclined part. The narrow epipleura are situated below this vertically inclined part of the elytra. In 
<taxonomicName authority="Lee &amp; Beenen, 2020" authorityName="Lee &amp; Beenen" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Taiwanoshaira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Taiwanoshaira" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Taiwanoshaira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. the elytra possess a margin that separates the horizontal elytral surface from the epipleura, which are inclined.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="129" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="129">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Maulik, 1936" authorityName="Maulik" authorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Shaira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Shaira" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Shaira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Maulik, S" journalOrPublisher="Taylor and Francis, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" refId="B8" refString="Maulik, S, 1936. The fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma. Coleoptera, Chrysomelidae (Galerucinae). Taylor and Francis, London" title="The fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma. Coleoptera, Chrysomelidae (Galerucinae)." year="1936">Maulik (1936)</bibRefCitation>
for brachelytrous 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Galerucinae">Galerucinae</taxonomicName>
with appendiculate claws and slender antennae. 
<bibRefCitation author="Beenen, R" journalOrPublisher="Entomologische Zeitschrift" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" pagination="173 - 183" refId="B1" refString="Beenen, R, 2013. New species and a new genus of brachelytrous Galerucinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Entomologische Zeitschrift 123: 173 - 183" title="New species and a new genus of brachelytrous Galerucinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae)." volume="123" year="2013">Beenen (2013)</bibRefCitation>
argued that 
<taxonomicName authority="Maulik, 1936" authorityName="Maulik" authorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Shaira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Shaira" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Shaira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be classified in 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" rank="tribe" tribe="Luperini">Luperini</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kimoto, S" editor="Sato, M" journalOrPublisher="The Association of the Memorial Issue of Emeritus Professor M. Chujo &amp; Biologial Laboratory, Nagoya Women's University, Nagoya" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" pagination="151 - 152" refId="B3" refString="Kimoto, S, 1982. Description of a new species of galerucid beetle from Taiwan, China (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). In: Sato, M, Ed., Special Issue to the Memory of Retirement of Emeritus Professor Michio Chujo. The Association of the Memorial Issue of Emeritus Professor M. Chujo &amp; Biologial Laboratory, Nagoya Women's University, Nagoya: 151 - 152" title="Description of a new species of galerucid beetle from Taiwan, China (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae)." volumeTitle="Special Issue to the Memory of Retirement of Emeritus Professor Michio Chujo." year="1982">Kimoto (1982)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. chujoi" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" rank="species" species="chujoi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">S. chujoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Taiwan and compared it with 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. maculata" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">S. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Maulik, 1936 from Manipur (India). 
<taxonomicName authority="Maulik, 1936" authorityName="Kimoto" authorityYear="1982" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Shaira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Shaira chujoi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chujoi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Shaira chujoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
somewhat resembles this species, but differs in having the body shorter and more oval, pronotum transverse and with different coloration. In fact, 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. chujoi" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" rank="species" species="chujoi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">S. chujoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should not have been included in the 
<taxonomicName authority="Maulik, 1936" authorityName="Maulik" authorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Shaira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Shaira" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Shaira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, because it differs in possessing entire elytra but the ridge is absent. We transfer it to the new genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Lee &amp; Beenen, 2020" authorityName="Lee &amp; Beenen" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Taiwanoshaira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Taiwanoshaira" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Taiwanoshaira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="129">
<taxonomicName authority="Lee &amp; Beenen, 2020" authorityName="Lee &amp; Beenen" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Taiwanoshaira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Taiwanoshaira" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Taiwanoshaira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. is likely not closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Maulik, 1936" authorityName="Maulik" authorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Shaira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Shaira" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Shaira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although also included in 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" rank="tribe" tribe="Luperini">Luperini</taxonomicName>
. It is unique and, although apterous, likely to be more closely related to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Duvivier, 1891" authorityName="Duvivier" authorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Sikkimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sikkimia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Sikkimia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Duvivier, 1891 with all bordered pronotal margins, two pairs of longitudinal furrows starting from base, one pair deeper and shorter near middle, the other pair longer but shallow near sides. This new genus is easily separated from 
<taxonomicName authority="Duvivier, 1891" authorityName="Duvivier" authorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Sikkimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sikkimia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Sikkimia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the open procoxal cavities and uniform antennae in both sexes (the closed procoxal cavities and modified antennomeres X and XI in males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Duvivier, 1891" authorityName="Duvivier" authorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Sikkimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sikkimia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Sikkimia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="129" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="129">
The new genus name combines 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Taiwan”">&quot;Taiwan&quot;</normalizedToken>
and &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Maulik, 1936" authorityName="Maulik" authorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Shaira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Shaira" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Shaira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; to indicate that this is a new genus endemic to Taiwan that is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Maulik, 1936" authorityName="Maulik" authorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Shaira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Shaira" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Shaira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The gender is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
